@node Foreword "Forword"
 FOREWORD:

This started off as a simple stats door that supported KFB as i use it, 
it became a bit more. =)
@ENDNODE

@node About "About this KewL util"
                         SuperStats v0.2b
 ABOUT:

Superstats is a scrolling stats door for maxs bbs and maxspro1+ series of 
bbs systems.

Its main advantage over other stats doors is that its scrolly and not
just static and it supports both internal and KFB file ratio detection.
 
@ENDNODE

@node Usage "Usage"
 USAGE:

Simply unpack superstats.lha to doors:

And from the bbs menu run doors:superstats/superstats.exe

CONFIG:

Theres a VERY basic config in this version.. u can select the speed for 
each stat that scrolls on the screen, ideal for adjusting faster modems, 
serials etc.

Each line in the config (doors:superstats/sstats.cfg) represents the stats 
that scrolls in order in the main program.
Please note @{B}DONT@{UB} use 0 or 00 in the config as it may crash 
the system @{B}YOU'VE BEEN WARNED!@{UB}

If you have a KFB filebase installed then Superstats will detect its 
presence and use the ratio from that file system.
 
@ENDNODE

@node History "MoooOOOoooo"
 HISTORY:

 v0.1 Internal and beta tester version.  Had basic scroll and no config.
 v0.2 Added config, nicer ansis.
@ENDNODE

@node future "were all gonna live on the moon, oh yes he will...ZZZzz"
 FUTURE:

I hopefully would like to continue superstats, but depending on 
feedback and the state of the bbs scene as a full im not too sure.

What i had planned are as follows.

More scrolling techniques including configuring scrolls for each 
stat(this is future-compatible now)
Configurable ansis, stats choices/settings
More filebase support i.e. FB/DFB/FLE etc..
Whatever else peeps ask for =)
Paragon compatability, i am currently upgrading this to work on S!X 
as most of my doors do as standard.
@ENDNODE

